articles.author: WAFAA SHURAFA and SAMY MAGDY
articles.description: DEIR AL-BALAH, Gaza Strip (AP) — Thousands of people broke into aid warehouses in Gaza to take flour and basic hygiene products, a U.N. agency said Sunday, in a mark of growing desperation and the breakdown of public order three weeks into the war between Israel and Gaza's militant Hamas rulers.
articles.title: Thousands loot UN aid warehouses in Gaza as death toll tops 8,000 and Israel widens ground offensive

articles.title: Thousands loot UN aid warehouses in Gaza as death toll tops 8,000 and Israel widens ground offensive

articles.author: NAJIB JOBAIN, SAMYA KULLAB and SAMY MAGDY
articles.description: KHAN YOUNIS, Gaza Strip (AP) — Two days after cellular and internet service abruptly vanished for most of Gaza amid a heavy Israeli bombardment, the crowded enclave was coming back online Sunday as communications systems were gradually being restored.
articles.title: Internet, phone service gradually returns after vanishing for most of Gaza amid heavy bombardment

articles.author: JULIA FRANKEL
articles.description: JERUSALEM (AP) — The Israeli military has sought to assure the public it can achieve the two goals of its war on Hamas simultaneously — toppling the strip's militant rulers and rescuing some 230 hostages abducted from Israel.
articles.title: Israel says its war can both destroy Hamas and rescue hostages. Their families are less certain

articles.author: BERNARD CONDON and JIM MUSTIAN
articles.description: Police across Maine were alerted just last month to “veiled threats” by the U.S. Army reservist who would go on to carry out the worst mass shooting in the state’s history, one of a string of missed red flags that preceded the massacre.
articles.title: Maine police were alerted weeks ago about shooter's threats

articles.description: LOS ANGELES (AP) — “Friends” star Matthew Perry, the Emmy-nominated actor whose sarcastic, but lovable Chandler Bing was among television’s most famous and most quotable characters, has died at 54.
articles.title: Matthew Perry, Emmy-nominated 'Friends' star, dead at 54

articles.author: TOM KRISHER, HALELUYA HADERO and COREY WILLIAMS
articles.description: DETROIT (AP) — Jeep maker Stellantis reached a tentative contract agreement with the United Auto Workers union on Saturday as it escalated strikes against General Motors by adding a plant in Tennessee.
articles.title: UAW and Stellantis reach tentative contract deal as union adds strike at Tennessee GM factory

articles.author: MEGAN JANETSKY
articles.description: ACAPULCO, Mexico (AP) — More resources are arriving on Mexico's battered Pacific coast, and the death toll from Hurricane Otis is growing as searchers recover more bodies from Acapulco's harbor and under fallen trees and other storm debris.
articles.title: More help arrives in Acapulco, and hurricane's death toll rises to 39 as searchers comb debris

articles.author: CAROLYN THOMPSON
articles.description: BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP) — They attend the same classes with access to the same programs, and even come from the same families. But girls consistently are outperforming boys, graduating at higher rates at public high schools around the country.
articles.title: Boys graduate high school at lower rates than girls, with lifelong consequences

articles.description: BEIJING (AP) — China’s foreign minister considers that the road to an expected meeting between President Xi Jinping and U.S. President Joe Biden would not be "smooth-sailing” and that both sides must work together to achieve results, the foreign ministry said on Sunday.
articles.title: China's foreign minister says Xi-Biden meeting in San Francisco would not be 'smooth-sailing'
